This paper is primarily focused on machine learning models, specifically neural networks, and their interpretability. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of explanations to train models, which falls under the category of Explainable AI, making cs.AI a likely sub-category as well. The paper also discusses natural language processing and the use of domain knowledge, which could fall under cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses the potential for adversarial attacks, which could fall under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Finally, the paper discusses the use of regularization to improve model performance, which could fall under cs.CV (Computer Vision).
